        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 3:38PM PDT by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA</headline>
        <description>At 337 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Granada Hills, or near Northridge, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
North Hills...
Panorama City...
Northridge...
Granada Hills...
Lakeview Terrace...
Arleta...
San Fernando...
Pacoima...
North Hollywood...
Van Nuys...
Sun Valley...
Sylmar...
Reseda...
Porter Ranch...
Sunland...
and Burbank.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
